                            <comment id="13573532" author="cgiera" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 14:24:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test with changed if worked on my side. I&apos;ve just added the fileName check to the if:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;				if ((disposition != null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (disposition
						.equalsIgnoreCase(Part.ATTACHMENT) || disposition
						.equalsIgnoreCase(Part.INLINE)))
						|| fileName != null) {
					LOG.debug(&quot;Mail contains file attachment: &quot; + fileName);
					// Parts marked with a disposition of Part.ATTACHMENT
					// are clearly attachments
					CollectionHelper.appendValue(map, fileName,
							part.getDataHandler());

				}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573535" author="cgiera" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 14:29:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I still use camel 2.6 due to some customer restrictions(java 5), but I couldn&apos;t find a branch for 2.6 to provide a patch for this version. So i will add a patch for the trunk version.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573538" author="cgiera" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 14:31:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch added&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13573554" author="davsclaus" created="Thu, 7 Feb 2013 14:53:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13744934" author="vitamon" created="Tue, 20 Aug 2013 13:02:30 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; ((disposition != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; (disposition.equalsIgnoreCase(Part.ATTACHMENT) || disposition.equalsIgnoreCase(Part.INLINE)))
                        || fileName != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a problem with the filename check:&lt;br/&gt;
If filename==null, but everything else is ok, it will be added to the map. There should be &quot;&amp;amp;&amp;amp; filename != null&quot;.&lt;br/&gt;
Please correct in future versions.  &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13776395" author="ceposta" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 15:34:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Vitalii, &lt;br/&gt;
Not sure the sub-task is valid. Can you review my comments on it?&lt;br/&gt;
Seems that since disposition is optional, it shouldn&apos;t make a difference if it&apos;s null or not and whether there is a fileName.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13776539" author="vitamon" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 17:40:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is not with disposition, but with fileName. I had a case when disposition was not null, but the fileName == null. (mail from Microsoft Exchange Server btw). The fileName should not be null in any case. Or the map entry (null -&amp;gt; part) will be added, which is not good and causes NPEs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13776549" author="vitamon" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 17:47:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s extract from my code:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Map&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt;, DataHandler&amp;gt; attachments = exchange.getIn().getAttachments();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (attachments.size() &amp;gt; 0) {
     &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; name : attachments.keySet()) {
         &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (StringUtils.isNotBlank(name)) { &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &amp;lt;--- added &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; to avoid &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; attachment names
&lt;/span&gt;            DataHandler dh = attachments.get(name);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13776553" author="ceposta" created="Tue, 24 Sep 2013 17:50:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, that makes sense. Thanks for the clarification. I&apos;ve attached a fix to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-6654&quot; title=&quot;Attachments with null filename should not be allowed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CAMEL-6654&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CAMEL-6654&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
